function minWastedSpace(packages, boxes) {
    const MOD = 1e9 + 7;
    packages = packages.sort((a, b) => a - b);
    let total_package_size = packages.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);
    let min_wasted_space = Infinity;

    for (let box_sizes of boxes) {
        box_sizes = box_sizes.sort((a, b) => a - b);
        if (box_sizes[box_sizes.length - 1] < packages[packages.length - 1]) {
            continue;
        }
        let wasted_space = 0;
        let pkg_idx = 0;
        for (let box_size of box_sizes) {
            pkg_idx = packages.findIndex((x, i) => i >= pkg_idx && x > box_size);
            if (pkg_idx === -1) {
                break;
            }
            wasted_space += box_size - packages[pkg_idx - 1];
        }
        min_wasted_space = Math.min(min_wasted_space, wasted_space);
    }
    return min_wasted_space === Infinity ? -1 : (total_package_size + min_wasted_space) % MOD;
}
```


    The algorithm first sorts the packages array in non-decreasing order.
It then calculates the total size of all packages and initializes the minimum wasted space to a large value. Remember that, the result needs to be returned modulo 1e9 + 7.
Iterating through the suppliers (boxes), it sorts the box sizes in non-decreasing order and checks if the largest box can contain the largest package. If not, we move on to the next supplier.
For each supplier, we iterate through their box sizes and for each box, we use binary search (upper_bound for C++ and bisect_right for Python) to find the first package that does not fit in the box. We then update the wasted space with the box size minus the largest package size that could fit in that box.
After iterating through all the suppliers, we return the minimum wasted space added to the total size of packages. If none of the suppliers can fit all the packages, we return -1.

solutionCode.java:
    ```java
import java.util.Arrays;

class Solution {
    public int minWastedSpace(int[] packages, int[][] boxes) {
        final int MOD = 1_000_000_007;
        Arrays.sort(packages);
        long total_package_size = 0;
        for (int package_size : packages) {
            total_package_size += package_size;
        }
        long min_wasted_space = Long.MAX_VALUE;

        for (int[] box_sizes : boxes) {
            Arrays.sort(box_sizes);
            if (box_sizes[box_sizes.length - 1] < packages[packages.length - 1]) {
                continue;
            }
            long wasted_space = 0;
            int pkg_idx = 0;
            for (int box_size : box_sizes) {
                int next_pkg_idx = Arrays.binarySearch(packages, pkg_idx, packages.length, box_size);
                if (next_pkg_idx >= 0) {
                    pkg_idx = next_pkg_idx;
                } else {
                    pkg_idx = -next_pkg_idx - 1;
                }
                wasted_space += box_size - packages[pkg_idx - 1];
            }
            min_wasted_space = Math.min(min_wasted_space, wasted_space);
        }
        return min_wasted_space == Long.MAX_VALUE ? -1 : (int) ((total_package_size + min_wasted_space) % MOD);
    }
}
```


